
	README FOR SFILE

    WARNING /!\: Is a very old program (code not clear), just maintained for
                 compile linux/macos, patch bugs and add small options.


	Search File : search file and search string in file.

  -Installation:
	$ tar zxvf sfile-x.x.x.tar.gz
	$ make
	$ ./sfile --help
	delete *.o:
	-----------
	$ make clean
	Need root:
	----------
	# make install
	$ sfile --help

  -Uninstall
	$ make uninstall

  -Arguments:
	  -h, --help               show usage and exit program
	  -v, --version            show program version and exit
	  -a, --all                do not ignore entries starting with '.'
	  -E, --env-path           search in directory to the $PATH varaible
	  -r, --recursive          list subdirectories recursively
	  -D, --ign-dir            do not list entries is dir
	  -F, --ign-file           do not list entries is regular file
	  -B, --ign-backup         do not list implied entries ending by '~'
	  -A, --ign-archive        do not list implied entries ending by
	                             .gz or .bz2 or .zip or .rar or .7z
	  -G, --ign-ext [EXT]      ignore all file ending by EXT
	  -P, --full-path          show full path to the entries
	  -c, --color              display file name with color
	  -I, --put-inode          print inode for file finds
	  -l, --line               print line to find word in file
	                           (just with -i argument)
	  -L, --info               print file information (perm, size, user)
	  -P, --print              print first line to find word
	  -V, --print-all          print all line to found word
	  -x, --exit [N]           exit program after N result finds
	  -o, --no-scan [STR]      do not list entries with STR in name
	  -e, --extension [STR]    search file by extension
	  -i, --in-file [STR]      search string to file
	  -N, --name [STR]         search file to name exactly with STR
	  -n, --in-name [STR]      if STR in the file name
	  -u, --uid [UID]          search file by UID
	  -Q, --inode [INODE]      search file by inode numbers
	      --ack [STRING]       like default ack program.
	                            active options: -VlPrci
	                           -V: Print all line where STRING (option -i)
	                           -l: Print line number
	                           -P: print file full path
	                           -r: recusive
	                           -i: search word in file
	                           -c: color
